  "text": "Adult Gad2-IRES-Cre;R26R-EYFP (Jax stock #010802 and #006148; n ϭ 6 males and 4 females, two to four months old) and Orexin-tTA mice (C57BL/6-Tg(orexin/ tTA)G5/Yamanaka; n ϭ 21 males, two to four months old), which express the tetracycline transactivator (tTA) exclusively in the Hcrt neurons [CITATION_1] , were singly-housed under a 12/12 h light/dark cycle with ad libitum access to food and water in temperature (24 Ϯ 2°C) and humidity (50 Ϯ 20% relative humidity) controlled rooms. Sixteen of the Orexin-tTA mice were reared with chow that included doxycycline (DOX). An additional cohort of C57BL/6J WT mice (Jax stock #000664; n ϭ 4 males and 4 females, three to six months old) were housed under the same conditions and used to assess the effects of clozapine-N-oxide (CNO) treatment on sleep/wake in naïve mice (Table 1 ). All studies were conducted in accordance with the Guide for the Care and Use of Laboratory Animals and were approved by the Institutional Animal Care and Use Committee at SRI International. Every effort was made to minimize animal discomfort throughout these studies.",
