      "span_text": "Adult Gad2-IRES-Cre;R26R-EYFP (Jax stock #010802 and #006148; n ϭ 6 males and 4 females, two to four months old) and Orexin-tTA mice (C57BL/6-Tg(orexin/ tTA)G5/Yamanaka; n ϭ 21 males, two to four months old), which express the tetracycline transactivator (tTA) exclusively in the Hcrt neurons, were singly-housed under a 12/12 h light/dark cycle with ad libitum access to food and water in temperature (24 Ϯ 2°C) and humidity (50 Ϯ 20% relative humidity) controlled rooms."
